---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
	title="Docs"
	description="Documentation for Tideway — a CSS design system delivered as agent skills."
	active="overview"
>
	<article class="doc">
		<p class="doc__eyebrow">Getting started</p>
		<h1 class="doc__title">Tideway documentation</h1>
		<p class="doc__lead">
			Tideway is a CSS design system delivered as conventions, not a library. Your coding agent
			follows a fixed set of design tokens and a strict BEM convention, and writes plain CSS you own.
		</p>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">Install</h2>
			<p class="doc__text">
				Tideway ships as agent skills. Install them into any coding agent with the
				<code class="doc__code">skills</code> CLI, or as a plugin in Claude Code — the
				<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/installation">Installation</a> page covers both. Prefer to skip
				the CLI? Point your agent at the setup file and it installs the skills, creates a
				<code class="doc__code">tokens.css</code>, and gets ready to style.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">How the docs are organized</h2>
			<div class="doc__list">
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Getting started</strong> — this overview and
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/installation">Installation</a>.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Skills</strong> — what each skill does and the rules it follows:
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/style">style</a> writes CSS,
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/review">review</a> checks it,
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/prune">prune</a> clears dead rules, and
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/migrate">migrate</a> moves an existing project onto Tideway.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Tokens</strong> — the fixed scales every value comes from:
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/colors">colors</a>,
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/spacing">spacing</a>, and more.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</article>
</DocsLayout>
